The SA Weather Service says it anticipates localised flooding over the weekend as thundershowers &amp; heavy rainfall continue. JOHANNESBURG The South African Weather Service says they anticipate localised flooding over the weekend as heavy rainfall is expected to continue.On Thursday, motorists driving through the Gilooly s Interchange were impacted by the rainfall.Affected areas also include Randburg, Roodepoort and Alberton where at least 20 houses have also been affected by the downpours.Forecaster Dipuo Tawana says, We re expecting the chances of rain to be a little bit higher. For Saturday we re looking at 60% probability of showers and thundershowers. There s a possibility that we might have localised flooding in places that we expect more rainfall on Saturday. On Sunday we re expecting a 60% chance of showers and thundershowers. 